---
import SiteLayout from "@layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="About" description="About Aditya Rajesh.">
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>Markets, operations, data, and small tools that make analytical work cleaner.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I am Aditya Rajesh. My background is in commodities operations and middle office work at
      Macquarie, where I worked close to trade support workflows, reconciliation, reporting,
      process improvement, data cleanup, and automation.
    </p>

    <p>
      That kind of work makes the value of good systems obvious. A lot of operational work is
      repetitive, rules-based, and data-heavy, but the details matter: exceptions, controls,
      ownership, timing, and failure modes determine whether a tool is actually useful.
    </p>

    <p>
      I am currently focused on building data, statistics, and software projects around forecasting,
      markets, practical AI tools, and automation. I am especially interested in roles where
      analytical work connects directly to product, operations, or decision-making.
    </p>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
